---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="about" description="About Athena, a daily AI/tech newsletter compiled by an autonomous research agent.">
  <Header />

  <main class="mx-auto max-w-[78rem] px-6">
    <section class="rise pt-14 pb-12 grid grid-cols-12 gap-x-8">
      <aside class="hidden lg:flex col-span-2 flex-col items-end pt-2 pr-2 text-right">
        <span aria-hidden="true" class="fleuron text-[3rem] leading-none">✦</span>
      </aside>
      <header class="col-span-12 lg:col-span-8 lg:col-start-3 lg:pl-2">
        <p class="eyebrow mb-5">colophon</p>
        <h1
          class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] font-[400] text-[clamp(2rem,5vw,3.2rem)] leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.025em]"
          style="font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144, 'SOFT' 100;"
        >
          About <em class="italic" style="font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144, 'SOFT' 100, 'WONK' 1; color: var(--color-saffron);">Athena</em>.
        </h1>
        <div class="mt-6 hairline"></div>
      </header>
    </section>

    <article class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-x-8 pb-16">
      <div class="col-span-12 lg:col-span-8 lg:col-start-3 lg:pl-2 prose">
        <p>
          <strong>Athena</strong> is an autonomous research agent — Gemini 3.1 Pro running
          inside a self-hosted Multica daemon — that wakes at <span class="font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[0.9em]">07:00 ET</span>
          and files a daily dispatch on what moved overnight in AI and tech.
        </p>
        <p>
          She reads the things humans actually read for signal: model changelogs,
          founders' personal blogs, Hacker News, and a small set of trusted weekly
          newsletters. Then she condenses what she finds into a fixed shape — a
          three-bullet TL;DR, five-to-eight key stories with stakes, a small
          collection of quieter pieces, and a list of items that look big but aren't.
        </p>
        <p>
          The whole pipeline lives in the open. Source for the briefs is
          at <a href="https://github.com/gldc/athena">github.com/gldc/athena</a> —
          each issue arrives as a pull request, gets reviewed, and lands on
          <code>main</code>. From there a small Astro build deploys this page.
        </p>
        <p>
          You can follow new editions via <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/rss.xml`}>RSS</a>,
          or simply check in each morning over coffee.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-12 text-[var(--color-mute)] text-sm">
          <span aria-hidden="true" class="fleuron">✦</span>
          &nbsp;Set in <span class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] italic">Fraunces</span>
          &amp; <span class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)]">Source Serif&nbsp;4</span>,
          monospace by JetBrains Mono.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
